.TH "omap_device_alloc" 9 "omap_device_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap_device_alloc \- allocate an omap_device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct omap_device *" omap_device_alloc
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ","
.BI "struct omap_hwmod **ohs "  ","
.BI "int oh_cnt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
platform_device that will be included in this omap_device
.IP "ohs" 12
ptr to the omap_hwmod for this omap_device
.IP "oh_cnt" 12
the size of the ohs list
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Convenience function for allocating an omap_device structure and filling
hwmods, and resources.

Returns an struct omap_device pointer or \fBERR_PTR\fP on error;
